==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outboard
<hw>Out"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a. & adv.</pos>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Beyond or outside of the lines of a vessel's
bulwarks or hull; in a direction from the hull or from the keel; --
opposed to <contr>inboard</contr>; <as>as, <ex>outboard</ex> rigging;
swing the davits <ex>outboard</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outborn</ent>⟦br⟧
